#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: effect-journal
---

# effect-journal — a 2-arg effect op next to a 1-arg op, one deep handler

Mirrors busi's Journal port (BUGS.md `v2-effect-multiarg-op`): `append` takes TWO
payload arguments, so the handler arm is `append/3` (scope, fact, resume). The
effect dispatch must deliver the payload args unpacked — packing them into one
tuple made the handler see `append/2` and die with "match: no arm for append/2".
`read` keeps the 1-arg shape so both arities cross the same handler.

## effect

```scalascript
effect Journal:
  def append(scope: String, fact: Int): Unit
  def read(scope: String): List[Int]
```

## runner — a deep handler collecting the append log

```scalascript
def runJournal[A](body: () => A): List[String] =
  handle { body() } {
    case Journal.append(scope, fact, resume) => (scope + "=" + fact) :: resume(())
    case Journal.read(scope, resume)         => resume(List(1, 2, 3))
    case Return(x)                           => List("ret=" + x)
  }
```
